1
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,318
- Hello.
- Hello, sweetie.

2
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:47,195
Daddy. lt's early.

3
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:51,234
l know. l just wanted you to know,
l'm sending you something.

4
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:56,790
- Does it smell nice?
- No, but it's sparkly.

5
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:03,712
- Does it have a receipt?
- l'm sending it to you from the store.

6
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,839
Come by. We'll have some breakfast.

7
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,235
lt would be a long trip.

8
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,674
l'm in Venice.

9
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,916
With your parole officer's approval?

10
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:22,999
l like the guy, Stella,
but we never really connected.

11
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:26,078
So l think l've paid my PO his last visit.

12
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:30,319
What are you into? Don't break
my heart. You said you were through.

13
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:33,034
After this, l am. l swear to you.

14
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:38,437
- ls Charlie there?
- l'm on a cellphone.

15
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:44,192
l'll call you tomorrow from a landline.
l love you. Go back to sleep. Bye.

16
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:47,035
Dad?

17
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:53,119
l love you, too.

18
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:02,274
- l sent it.
- You're supposed to shop after the job.

19
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:06,109
l feel so optimistic. How do you feel?

20
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,832
- Fine.
- Fine?

21
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:12,350
- You know what fine stands for?
- Yeah, unfortunately.

22
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,232
- Freaked-out...
- lnsecure...

23
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,635
- Neurotic...
- And emotional.

24
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:20,992
- See those columns behind you?
- What about them?

25
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,988
That's where they strung up
thieves who felt fine.

26
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,714
Well, after you.

27
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:37,588
- For after the haul.
- Hope l'll get to fire it up.

28
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,756
No word from the garbage men?

29
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:44,795
No. They don't show, prep's wasted
and you're out of retirement for nothing.

30
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:51,519
This is fun. You've taken over the reins,
the worries. l'm just along for the ride.

31
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,756
Glad you're enjoying yourself, John.

32
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,953
Police boat can get to us in seven, so
you've four minutes to work your magic.

33
00:04:58,160 --> 00:05:02,756
- You told me ten and said l'd have five.
- When?

34
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,551
Do not mess with me.

35
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:11,070
- l will kick your ass.
- Yeah? Take your best shot.

36
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,554
What?

37
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:26,351
Come on, let's go.
What is it this time?

38
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,120
Da Vinci. Architect, engineer, painter.

39
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:31,550
- Fascinating.
- Check this out.

40
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:36,356
''Learn the language of poetry,
art, romance, sex...''

41
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:40,314
Unlike you, my friend, l don't need
a guidebook. Can we go?

42
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:44,798
- Right, guvnor.
- Make yourself useful. Untie that line.

43
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,036
- Today.
- Yeah.

44
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:50,710
Yeah, Gilligan, if you don't mind.

45
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,154
We set?

46
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,511
Yeah. The viewing matrix
tracks the Cartesian coordinates

47
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,632
and altitude angles
to give the exact position of our baby.

48
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:37,515
- We're in ltaly. Speak English.
- Steve, how we looking?

49
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:42,032
Papa took the boat at 8.1 5,
so the garage is empty.

50
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:46,472
Mama left with daughter at 8.30
for pre-school, as usual,

51
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:50,116
so for the next 45 minutes,
we own this place.

52
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,436
Still no word from the garbage men?

53
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:56,792
Who got you the Budapest beekeepers?
You can trust these guys.

54
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,355
How many times must l tell you?

55
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:03,599
Trust everyone,
but not the devil inside them.

56
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,996
We're in.

57
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,434
Just tell me where to paint.

58
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:20,192
- Your men still not in position?
- They will be.

59
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,153
You don't know that. We should abort.

60
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,920
l think that's Charlie's call now.

61
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:35,719
Our baby's being taken away tonight.
This is our only shot.

62
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:40,950
- Charlie?
- Keep going?

63
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:44,758
- lt's up to you, kid.
- Let's go.

64
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,391
OK, Steve.

65
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:55,073
From the west wall,
measure 1 4 feet 8 inches.

66
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:59,559
- Got it.
- 8 feet 5 inches from the north wall.

67
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:02,513
That's the northwest corner of our baby.

68
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:05,792
- Got it.
- Well, it's right above you.

69
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:42,874
Now, paint. 2 feet 9 inches wide,
2 feet 5 inches deep.

70
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:48,630
OK, Left Ear, you're up.
1 4 feet 4 inches from that west wall.

71
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:22,598
The garbage men are in position, John.

72
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,395
They've got the safe in the boat!

73
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:23,555
Someone just called it in.
The police boat's heading your way.

74
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:26,433
Seven minutes and counting. Let's go.

75
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,670
We've got four minutes. Let's go.

76
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:52,032
Hey, you guys. Come here.

77
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,872
l want to propose a toast.

78
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,036
To us!

79
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,994
And l want to propose a toast to Charlie.

80
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:09,432
We just stole 35 million dollars worth
of gold without even holding a gun

81
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:11,676
because he planned this down to a T.

82
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:14,917
Nobody else could've done that. Charlie!

83
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:22,638
So, come on. Shopping lists. Who's
doing what? Spare no dirty details.

84
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:29,439
Come on, guys. Take a lesson from
an old man. Don't spend it. lnvest.

85
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:32,359
- ln what?
- ln gold.

86
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:39,716
- Let's get out of here first.
- What are you getting, Rob?

87
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,639
l don't know.
There's a lot of things you can buy.

88
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:48,756
l'm thinking of naked girls and leather
seats. l'll get the Aston Martin Vanquish.

89
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,997
There's little a girl
won't do in one of those.

90
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:58,275
l'm getting a NAD T7 70 digital decoder,
70-watt amps and Burr-Brown DACs.

91
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:03,315
lt's a big stereo with speakers so loud
they blow women's clothes off.

92
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:06,751
$35 million and you can't get more
creative than that?

93
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:10,316
l'm going to Andalusia, south of Spain,

94
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:15,913
get me a big house, a library
of first editions, a room for my shoes.

95
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:19,271
- What about you, Steve?
- l haven't decided yet.

96
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:22,870
You haven't decided yet?!
ls it the mountain air?

97
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:26,914
l liked what you said.
l'll take one each of yours.

98
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,957
Well, two of everything for Steve.

99
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:41,150
l loved the toast. But you could've
pulled this off with your eyes closed.

100
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:43,749
You were just incredible.

101
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:47,669
You saw the whole picture
and covered all the angles.

102
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:52,670
Charlie, there are two kinds
of thieves in this world.

103
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,474
The ones who steal
to enrich their lives,

104
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:58,752
and the ones who steal
to define their lives.

105
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:04,318
Don't be the latter. You miss out
on what's really important in this life.

106
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:08,516
What are you talking about?
You've been a good father.

107
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:12,030
Sitting in prisons
doesn't make you a good father.

108
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:17,997
l've spent half my kid's life in prison.
Don't get to my age with only this.

109
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:25,559
Find somebody you want to spend the
rest of your life with. And hold on to her.

110
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:28,957
Hey, let's go. l'm freezing my ass off.

111
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:35,679
- Steve's getting cold. You, too?
- l'm all right.

112
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:42,077
- l love you, kid. You did really great.
- Thanks, John.

113
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:44,996
Let's go.

114
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,750
Rob was driving that boat
like Don Johnson!

115
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:16,669
- Yeah, from Brixton.
- What do you know about Brixton?

116
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:26,311
Look at this idiot
in the middle of the road.

117
00:20:26,520 --> 00:20:28,158
What's this?

118
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,160
Who the hell are these guys?

119
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:39,311
- Take your hands off the wheel.
- Steve.

120
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,877
Just do it.

121
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,999
No, John.

122
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:54,193
- What the hell are you doing?
- Made a few plans of my own.

123
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:58,433
There's nowhere you can go
we won't find you.

124
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,517
l think that's probably right.

125
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:03,077
Go! Go!

126
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,913
We've got to go, Charlie.

127
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:12,118
- Do you always work in the dark?
- Makes me feel l'm alone.

128
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,996
Not bad, Stella.

129
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,998
- Purley couldn't crack that safe.
- Neither could Spears.

130
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:22,998
- You know who to call first.
- You're expensive.

131
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:26,670
Those guys cut us a break
on subpoena jobs, goodwill...

132
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:30,589
l do it for the money.
l'll send you a bill.

133
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:33,997
- Don't you want to see inside?
- l never look inside.

134
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:36,430
Have a good day. Hey, George.

135
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,793
- How long to crack it?
- Four minutes, 43 seconds.

136
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,434
- You're the man.
- What's in the line-up?

137
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:20,395
Todd Millikan called. He has
a prototype lock he wants you to test.

138
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:23,239
He added two false contact points
on the tumbler.

139
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:26,238
l'll pretend to be stumped
for a second or two.

140
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:31,594
And there's a Charlie Croker in your
office. Says you know each other.

141
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:38,716
- Charlie Croker.
- Hi, Stella.

142
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:44,791
Didn't l tell you
l never want to see you again?

143
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:51,314
lt was when you told me my father died
after you pulled him in for one last job.

144
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:59,153
We found him, Stella.
He's in Los Angeles.

145
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:03,672
The gold bricks he stole from us had
a Balinese dancer stamped on them.

146
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:08,271
My contact, Skinny Pete, says an LA
dealer's been buying those bricks.

147
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:13,156
- How do you know it's him?
- Skinny Pete sent me this.

148
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:16,158
Steve changed his last name to Frizelli.

149
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:25,028
- Why tell me this?
- l checked high-end safe companies.

150
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:28,118
Steve had a Worthington 1 000
delivered to his home office.

151
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:32,199
You install a Worthington 1 000 only
if you've got something big to guard.

152
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:36,473
No one on my crew can handle it.
l need somebody l can trust.

153
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:39,353
l'm a safe technician. l'm not a thief.

154
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:44,793
lt's not about the gold, Stella.
John was like a father to me, too.

155
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:51,110
l'm sorry. l can't move on
until l've set things right.

156
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,475
l've moved on.

157
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:03,074
Come on, then, Charlie. Come on.

158
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:13,632
l want to see his face
when his gold is gone.

159
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,798
He took my father, l'm taking this.

160
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,715
- She's in.
- That's a good thing?

161
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:26,559
She can crack the Worthington 1 000
without flinching.

162
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:29,194
l'm not sure
hiring a civilian's a good idea.

163
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:32,995
- She's got the skills and the motivation.
- Exactly.

164
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:36,192
She's emotional.
You know what happens then.

165
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:41,394
Don't kid yourself. We're all
emotional on this one. Let's go.

166
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:45,158
- Are you ready?
- Course l am.

167
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:48,038
You're not ready.

168
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:15,074
- That was quick.
- Where are they?

169
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:19,876
We're a little early.
l didn't expect us to get here that fast.

170
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:23,470
There. That's Lyle.
He's my computer genius.

171
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:33,073
He's who really invented Napster.
At least, that's how he tells it.

172
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:36,955
Said Shawn Fanning was his college
room-mate and stole his idea.

173
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:52,110
l think it's his first time
riding that bike, though.

174
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:02,271
- You OK?
- Yeah.

175
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:07,949
That's Left Ear.
Demolition and explosives.

176
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:11,948
When he was ten he put too many
M80s in the toilet bowl.

177
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:17,955
- Cool! How did you do that?
- What?

178
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:22,233
- How did you do that?
- What?

179
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:24,670
What?

180
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:28,429
Lost hearing in his right ear.
Blown stuff up ever since.

181
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:34,034
Handsome Rob. Premier wheelman.

182
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:38,438
Once drove from LA just so
he could set the freeway chase record.

183
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:50,874
He got 1 1 0 love letters from women
who saw him on the news.

184
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:05,789
And you? l never heard
how you got your start.

185
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:10,312
Me? Well, l've been a thief
since l had baby teeth.

186
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:16,152
- OK, you both know what to do.
- Cough it up now.

187
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:25,912
Watch it, spas!
What's your problem, man?

188
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,792
- Hey, Charlie.
- Good to see you.

189
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,230
Good to see you.

190
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:38,908
- Hello, Charlie.
- You good?

191
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:41,429
Guys, Stella Bridger.

192
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:46,752
- Nice to meet you.
- Phones.

193
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:52,159
They're all clean, with internal chips.
Change daily, we will get heat online.

194
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:54,430
lDs?

195
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:59,396
James Hymen?
One time give me a cool name.

196
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:02,433
- 1 40 pounds? Try 1 65.
- Try lifting some weights.

197
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:06,474
- Try lifting up these.
- We leave tomorrow, all right?

198
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:15,229
- Handsome, help him with the bike.
- Help Knievel set up his next jump.

199
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:46,638
Out of all the places for a thief to hide,
this joker picked Hollywood.

200
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:48,831
He's a punk, but he ain't stupid.

201
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:53,875
We need a way to make a blueprint
of the inside of Steve's house.

202
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:57,277
- l want phone surveillance.
- l want to try something.

203
00:32:57,480 --> 00:33:01,439
l'll fool the phone company into
thinking there's a legal tap on the line

204
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:06,111
and re-route the copies of the calls to us.
Been doing it to my ex for years.

205
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:10,711
How long...will it take? Not, how
long have you been doing it to your ex?

206
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:15,675
- l'll have it running by morning.
- Sorry l'm late.

207
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:19,919
We gotta get Steve out of the house.
How much time do you need?

208
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:22,873
- Five minutes flat.
- Don't be cocky.

209
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:26,356
lt's not the same as opening a safe
for the police.

210
00:33:26,560 --> 00:33:32,112
Perspiration on your fingertips, heart's
pounding. Whole different ball game.

211
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:35,551
l appreciate your concern. l'll be fine.

212
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:39,070
This is the easy part.
The getaway can get us caught.

213
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:42,033
- What's the schedule?
- Drive to Union Station.

214
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:47,712
Car goes onto the train. We need to
know exactly how long to Union Station.

215
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:22,030
- Oh, great. Carson security system.
- How good is it?

216
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:26,313
Carson's hold an annual contest.
$50,000 if you can bypass the system.

217
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:31,958
lt's a who's who of ex-cons.
Five years running, no one's been paid.

218
00:34:32,160 --> 00:34:34,071
Here's the status.

219
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:37,317
An anti-scaling fence,
hardened electro-plated steel.

220
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:40,478
l'll have to paint that up
with some nitromon.

221
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:45,879
- Security?
- A little rent-a-cop with a 9 mm.

222
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:49,834
That security booth looks prime
for a chemical grenade.

223
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:53,316
Nitromon, chemical grenades?
That stuff's hard to come by.

224
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:58,548
Yeah, Lyle, it's a bear market... Shit!

225
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:05,468
This dude got dogs. l don't do dogs.
l had a real bad experience.

226
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:11,676
- What happened?
- l had a bad experience. l'm deaf?!

227
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:33,958
''Turn in your badge
