- You swear to God?
- You're crazy. l swear to God, l didn't.

462
01:00:43,600 --> 01:00:46,160
Well, then, l guess l believe you.

463
01:01:34,760 --> 01:01:38,912
Let's putt it. Putt, not drive.

464
01:01:39,120 --> 01:01:43,477
Very good. You can get it.
l know you can do it.

465
01:01:44,840 --> 01:01:48,355
- Here to see Skinny Pete.
- He's over there.

466
01:01:48,560 --> 01:01:50,596
Thanks, man.

467
01:01:52,280 --> 01:01:55,989
Don't stare.
He doesn't like people staring.

468
01:01:56,200 --> 01:01:57,952
Stare at what?

469
01:01:58,160 --> 01:02:01,994
That was good. Try that one.
l know you'll get that one.

470
01:02:02,200 --> 01:02:04,919
- That was great.
- Skinny Pete.

471
01:02:05,120 --> 01:02:08,476
- Yo, Charlie.
- What's up, man?

472
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:10,875
Was l right about the gold?

473
01:02:11,080 --> 01:02:14,595
l'm not here for that.
We need some supplies.

474
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:18,952
Baby, go relax. Go relax!

475
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:30,719
- Supplies.
- What's wrong?

476
01:02:32,120 --> 01:02:35,669
Some nitromon...

477
01:02:35,880 --> 01:02:40,351
- Some nitromon primer.
- What's wrong?

478
01:02:41,680 --> 01:02:45,753
Nothing, l'm cool. l'm great.
l just need a big can of...

479
01:02:45,960 --> 01:02:48,394
...nitromon primer, detonating cord,

480
01:02:48,600 --> 01:02:50,431
two triple-charger chemical grenades
and a launcher.

481
01:02:50,640 --> 01:02:54,918
- Right, like l had told you earlier.
- All right.

482
01:03:00,560 --> 01:03:06,749
- Cost you about five Gs.
- Done. Thanks. Sorry about that.

483
01:03:06,960 --> 01:03:10,794
- All right, man. Peace.
- Come on.

484
01:03:27,360 --> 01:03:29,237
Get out.

485
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:32,195
There.

486
01:03:39,720 --> 01:03:42,075
Vance has something to tell you.

487
01:03:44,840 --> 01:03:46,910
Go on.

488
01:03:48,320 --> 01:03:51,232
A couple of weeks back...

489
01:03:51,440 --> 01:03:53,954
...l was working in your cousin's shop.

490
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:58,438
A guy come in asking about gold
bricks with Balinese dancer on.

491
01:03:58,640 --> 01:04:03,714
- What did you tell him?
- That l'd seen the bricks.

492
01:04:08,760 --> 01:04:14,153
- l'm sorry.
- What did this man look like?

493
01:04:15,440 --> 01:04:19,672
He had long black hair
with tattoo on his neck.

494
01:04:22,240 --> 01:04:24,993
He must have weighed
at least 400 pounds.

495
01:04:25,200 --> 01:04:28,431
l know that guy.

496
01:04:53,960 --> 01:04:55,996
Baby, go relax.

497
01:05:06,040 --> 01:05:09,874
- Do you know who l am?
- You're Mashkov.

498
01:05:10,080 --> 01:05:16,030
Right. You were asking about the gold
bricks with the Balinese dancer on.

499
01:05:17,040 --> 01:05:18,439
Why?

500
01:05:25,800 --> 01:05:28,837
Steve just confirmed
his eight o'clock dinner reservation.

501
01:05:29,040 --> 01:05:33,079
- Let's go over it.
- Gas the guards. Doors open, 8.1 5.

502
01:05:33,280 --> 01:05:36,989
- Safe popped by 8.25.
- Loaded, 8.35. Out, 8.45.

503
01:05:37,200 --> 01:05:38,918
Straight to Union Station.

504
01:05:39,120 --> 01:05:42,669
Only green lights, rest of city's red.
Cops stuck in traffic.

505
01:05:42,880 --> 01:05:48,318
Train leaves at 1 0. Cars must be
aboard by 9.30. Timing must be exact.

506
01:05:48,520 --> 01:05:51,398
- Let's get ready.
- Let's get it.

507
01:06:20,840 --> 01:06:25,960
Wow, that is a nice car. Sorry, Rob.
Coast is clear, guys.

508
01:06:37,440 --> 01:06:40,318
This is it. Moment of truth.

509
01:06:41,200 --> 01:06:45,955
What the hell is this? Shit!

510
01:06:46,160 --> 01:06:49,596
Steve's neighbour's throwing a party.

511
01:06:51,360 --> 01:06:55,399
- Are you here for the Baker party, sir?
- No.

512
01:06:57,160 --> 01:07:00,675
We're not blowing any gates tonight,
guys. Too many witnesses.

513
01:07:00,880 --> 01:07:05,749
- Stella.
- l know...

514
01:07:05,960 --> 01:07:07,712
l'm late for my date.

515
01:07:07,920 --> 01:07:13,313
You've got to be charming. We need
him to ask you out again. Sorry.

516
01:07:13,760 --> 01:07:16,832
Let's get out of the street.

517
01:07:19,920 --> 01:07:23,708
- l can't imagine you doing that.
- What's that mean?

518
01:07:23,920 --> 01:07:28,596
Well, you don't really seem
the adventurous type, you know.

519
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:31,837
Don't let the cable uniform throw you.

520
01:07:32,040 --> 01:07:34,634
l wasn't making assumptions.

521
01:07:34,840 --> 01:07:39,914
- l've made some about you.
- Oh, really? And...?

522
01:07:42,040 --> 01:07:44,998
You're just going to have to wait and see.

523
01:07:50,760 --> 01:07:54,469
Why wait? Let's go back to my place.
No assumptions.

524
01:07:54,680 --> 01:07:57,513
Not tonight. lt's late. l should go home.

525
01:07:58,760 --> 01:08:01,479
- You have a cable company curfew?
- No.

526
01:08:01,680 --> 01:08:08,199
l've made some bad calls in the past.
We should take this slower.

527
01:08:08,400 --> 01:08:11,915
Lovely dinner, sparkling conversation.
Still don't trust me?

528
01:08:12,120 --> 01:08:18,832
l trust everyone. lt's the devil
inside them l don't trust.

529
01:08:22,840 --> 01:08:27,356
That's an interesting saying.
Where'd you pick that up?

530
01:08:27,560 --> 01:08:32,270
- Can't remember.
- l knew a guy who said it just like that.

531
01:08:32,480 --> 01:08:34,596
- Really?
- Yeah.

532
01:08:34,800 --> 01:08:40,113
He's the only person l've ever heard
say that. His name was John Bridger.

533
01:08:41,360 --> 01:08:45,797
- You're hurting me.
- He had a daughter about your age.

534
01:08:49,360 --> 01:08:50,679
Let go.

535
01:08:50,880 --> 01:08:53,394
l knew there was something familiar
about you.

536
01:08:53,600 --> 01:08:58,116
You're exactly like your old man.
l liked him, too.

537
01:08:58,320 --> 01:09:02,598
l liked him right up
until the minute l shot him.

538
01:09:02,800 --> 01:09:04,870
Who are you working with?

539
01:09:09,920 --> 01:09:12,593
She's with us.

540
01:09:22,440 --> 01:09:26,991
- The gang's all here.
- The only thing worse than a thief...

541
01:09:27,200 --> 01:09:28,679
...is a coward.

542
01:09:28,880 --> 01:09:34,034
Then you should've seen the way
your daddy begged for his life.

543
01:09:34,240 --> 01:09:38,028
- He's not worth it.
- Put a leash on your cat.

544
01:09:46,080 --> 01:09:48,230
Not bad, Charlie.

545
01:09:48,440 --> 01:09:53,355
You have no idea how hard it is
for me not to kill you now.

546
01:09:53,560 --> 01:09:57,348
You know better than that.
You can't let emotion into these things.

547
01:09:57,560 --> 01:10:00,199
lt wasn't emotion
when you shot John and left us?

548
01:10:00,400 --> 01:10:04,109
That wasn't about emotion.
lt was about a lot of gold.

549
01:10:04,320 --> 01:10:06,754
Anything you think you deserved,
you didn't.

550
01:10:06,960 --> 01:10:11,556
Don't talk about right and wrong
with me. l don't give a shit. OK?

551
01:10:11,760 --> 01:10:16,390
You got your cards, l got mine.
We made our play, l came out on top.

552
01:10:16,600 --> 01:10:21,151
lf you want to start the game
up again, that's fine with me.

553
01:10:21,360 --> 01:10:23,999
What is your play here, really?

554
01:10:24,200 --> 01:10:27,078
Come on, what do you think?

555
01:10:27,280 --> 01:10:31,876
You'll try to take out my guards?
l have five that you don't know about.

556
01:10:32,080 --> 01:10:36,676
You'll have Lyle hack the system?
l'll change it tomorrow morning.

557
01:10:36,880 --> 01:10:43,069
What was your final move? Have
Bridger's daughter try to crack my safe?

558
01:10:43,280 --> 01:10:48,832
That's very poetic, but l just don't
think she'll get anywhere near it.

559
01:10:49,040 --> 01:10:52,430
Same old Steve.
Always thinking defensively.

560
01:10:52,640 --> 01:10:54,790
That's why you're always number two.

561
01:10:55,000 --> 01:10:58,197
- How's that?
- You've got no imagination.

562
01:10:58,400 --> 01:11:02,109
Couldn't even decide what to buy.
Bought what everyone else wanted.

563
01:11:02,320 --> 01:11:07,235
- Try this. That gold is already gone.
- Bullshit.

564
01:11:07,440 --> 01:11:11,069
lt's over, Charlie.
l'm trying to move the last two bricks.

565
01:11:11,280 --> 01:11:15,273
You want to come after me over
a couple of lousy bricks? Be my guest.

566
01:11:15,480 --> 01:11:20,998
But you're off to a bad start because
you just blew the element of surprise.

567
01:11:25,040 --> 01:11:28,112
Surprised?

568
01:11:28,320 --> 01:11:32,233
lt's over when l say it's over.

569
01:11:34,800 --> 01:11:37,155
Are you all right, sir?

570
01:12:06,960 --> 01:12:08,837
How you doing?

571
01:12:10,480 --> 01:12:12,436
Good.

572
01:12:13,080 --> 01:12:18,871
Considering the fact l'm doing
all of this for a man l barely knew.

573
01:12:26,280 --> 01:12:30,273
You know what bothered me
all those years?

574
01:12:30,480 --> 01:12:36,032
lt was that whenever he'd call me
to tell me he was on some job,

575
01:12:36,240 --> 01:12:39,471
l knew you were right there with him.

576
01:12:43,040 --> 01:12:46,555
You got to know him a lot better
than l did.

577
01:12:47,440 --> 01:12:50,477
Doesn't mean he wasn't
thinking about you.

578
01:12:50,680 --> 01:12:54,116
- Would be nice if it was true.
- lt is.

579
01:12:54,320 --> 01:12:59,394
He always regretted not having been
a good enough father to you.

580
01:13:01,160 --> 01:13:04,436
- How do you know?
- Because he told me.

581
01:13:11,000 --> 01:13:14,037
What did you do to your hand?

582
01:13:16,080 --> 01:13:21,473
- l punched Steve.
- Why do you get to punch him?

583
01:13:23,480 --> 01:13:26,199
'Cause those hands
are way too valuable.

584
01:13:39,360 --> 01:13:40,634
You OK?

585
01:13:49,200 --> 01:13:52,988
There'll be nothing left of that
if you keep rubbing it.

586
01:13:57,000 --> 01:13:59,798
Tell Mr Frizelli we'll see him at eight.

587
01:14:03,760 --> 01:14:06,957
- He's flying the coop.
- When?

588
01:14:07,760 --> 01:14:10,593
His security guard
called for a helicopter at 4 p.m.

589
01:14:10,800 --> 01:14:13,155
and an armoured car at five.

590
01:14:13,360 --> 01:14:18,309
There's a cargo plane, departing LAX
at 8 p.m. to Mexico City.

591
01:14:18,520 --> 01:14:21,114
What if he's moving
the safe as a diversion?

592
01:14:21,320 --> 01:14:25,836
- We crack it, the gold's somewhere else.
- Steve won't let it out of his sight.

593
01:14:26,040 --> 01:14:28,998
lt'll be in that truck
and he'll watch it from the helicopter.

594
01:14:29,200 --> 01:14:32,556
- The gold's headed to Mexico?
- Who knows...?

595
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:37,959
- Slow down. This is good news for us.
- What do you mean?

596
01:14:38,160 --> 01:14:42,312
Now the safe has come to us.
We're going to boost it in transit.

597
01:14:42,520 --> 01:14:44,431
He could take a dozen routes.

598
01:14:44,640 --> 01:14:48,349
We don't know which. We can't take
out an armoured truck at rush hour.

599
01:14:48,560 --> 01:14:54,112
We're already set up to do it. Gridlock
every route except the one we choose.

600
01:14:54,320 --> 01:14:56,834
Force that truck
to go where we want.

601
01:14:57,040 --> 01:15:00,555
Where do we want it to go?
We'd lose a shoot up.

602
01:15:00,760 --> 01:15:03,479
We do it like The ltalian Job.

603
01:15:10,000 --> 01:15:11,877
- Why'd you do it?
- Do what?

604
01:15:12,080 --> 01:15:16,358
- Yevhen. You didn't have to clip him.
- We didn't clip anybody.

605
01:15:16,560 --> 01:15:20,075
Yevhen's cousin is
under the impression you did.

606
01:15:20,280 --> 01:15:21,554
Why?

607
01:15:21,760 --> 01:15:24,274
Because you wanted
to know about the gold.

608
01:15:24,480 --> 01:15:26,914
You told him that?

609
01:15:27,120 --> 01:15:30,556
One thing l know,
never mess with Mother Nature,

610
01:15:30,760 --> 01:15:34,230
mother-in-laws,
or mother-freaking Ukrainians.

611
01:15:34,440 --> 01:15:36,590
Look, l need a favour.

612
01:16:02,760 --> 01:16:07,038
Had a hiccup last night. Need some help.
More hands-on. lnterested?

613
01:16:07,240 --> 01:16:12,473
Could be, but l don't like
to be kept in the dark. lf l'm in, l'm in.

614
01:16:12,680 --> 01:16:16,389
- OK, you're in.
- All right.

615
01:16:19,120 --> 01:16:23,033
- What do you think?
- This'll work. Let's go.

616
01:16:33,040 --> 01:16:36,669
You're amazing. lt's a work of genius.

617
01:16:45,360 --> 01:16:48,193
- You OK?
- Just give me a moment.

618
01:16:48,400 --> 01:16:52,916
- Now?
- l'm inserting this pin into the detonator.

619
01:16:53,120 --> 01:16:58,672
lf the brass touches the sides, we'll
both be the last people we ever see.

620
01:16:58,880 --> 01:17:01,155
Take all the time you need.

621
01:17:04,240 --> 01:17:07,198
- Hey, Charlie.
- What?

622
01:17:08,560 --> 01:17:10,915
l love you, man.

623
01:17:12,240 --> 01:17:14,117
l love you, too.

624
01:17:20,560 --> 01:17:23,313
He's going to be on train 59
for New Orleans.

625
01:17:23,520 --> 01:17:25,317
You sure the source is good?

626
01:17:25,520 --> 01:17:26,953
l'm sure.

627
01:17:51,760 --> 01:17:53,637
Check positions. Napster?

628
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:55,717
l'm in position.

629
01:17:57,160 --> 01:18:01,950
- Handsome Rob?
- ln position. Everything's quiet, Charlie.

630
01:18:04,440 --> 01:18:05,714
Wrench?

631
01:18:06,440 --> 01:18:07,714
Set.

632
01:18:23,280 --> 01:18:27,671
We've got an uninvited visitor. There's
a motorcycle guard following the truck.

633
01:18:27,880 --> 01:18:29,836
We'll deal with it.

634
01:18:35,600 --> 01:18:37,795
- Who are they?
- What's wrong?

635
01:18:38,000 --> 01:18:42,437
You won't believe this.
He's brought in three armoured trucks.

636
01:18:42,640 --> 01:18:44,835
lt's a shell game now.

637
01:18:45,040 --> 01:18:47,873
l can't re-route
if l don't know which to re-route.

638
01:18:48,080 --> 01:18:50,196
Follow the one Steve
follows by helicopter.

639
01:18:50,400 --> 01:18:53,358
He'll never
let that gold out of his sight.

640
01:18:53,560 --> 01:18:56,996
Unless he's playing us. And he is.

641
01:19:06,360 --> 01:19:09,033
OK, let's go! Move it out!

642
01:19:22,280 --> 01:19:25,192
Here we go. They're pulling out.

643
01:19:26,480 --> 01:19:29,677
Napster, pull up the traffic
cameras you're watching.

644
01:19:29,880 --> 01:19:32,348
Where's the first camera they go past?

645
01:19:36,240 --> 01:19:40,028
- Vine and Yucca.
- See which one's riding low.

646
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:55,954
First in line...
First two are the same, so...

647
01:20:00,080 --> 01:20:02,594
Houston, we have our truck.
Number 1 28.

648
01:20:11,360 --> 01:20:14,113
We're moving out.

649
01:20:14,720 --> 01:20:17,678
Three Kilo Bob to Two Fox Mike,
we're heading to the airport.

650
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:36,276
OK, guys, truck 1 28
has turned right heading west.

651
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:38,596
Gridlock time.

652
01:20:47,120 --> 01:20:49,156
We've crashed.

653
01:20:49,720 --> 01:20:52,075
lt's not a crash.

654
01:20:52,960 --> 01:20:56,589
- We've got power.
- l can't log in.

655
01:20:57,400 --> 01:21:00,870
They're about to hit a detour
and be sent your way.

656
01:21:13,120 --> 01:21:18,592
You'll never shut down the real Napster.

657
01:21:26,160 --> 01:21:29,232
What's your problem?!

658
01:21:33,480 --> 01:21:38,759
- Truck 1 28, what is your progress?
- Traffic's out of control.

659
01:21:38,960 --> 01:21:40,678
We've got to look for another route.

660
01:21:41,600 --> 01:21:43,955
Check the police band.

661
01:21:44,160 --> 01:21:47,197
OK, l'm opening up a space
on Highland.

662
01:21:50,480 --> 01:21:52,516
- Get us out of here.
- l'm trying.

663
01:21:58,200 --> 01:22:00,839
And he's taking it.

664
01:22:04,720 --> 01:22:08,713
Police are saying computers
are down at traffic control.

665
01:22:08,920 --> 01:22:12,515
Nice, Charlie. What are you up to?

666
01:22:12,720 --> 01:22:14,756
Go back.

667
01:22:22,640 --> 01:22:25,359
l now command you to turn left.

668
01:22:26,760 --> 01:22:30,116
Come on, take the left.

669
01:22:30,320 --> 01:22:32,993
Yeah, you did. You did.

670
01:23:05,840 --> 01:23:07,398
Give us the flag.

671
01:23:08,720 --> 01:23:13,794
Metro just passed through the station.
You are clear for 90 seconds. Go.

672
01:23:28,160 --> 01:23:29,479
Come on, Steve.

673
01:23:52,680 --> 01:23:55,240
30 seconds and counting.

674
01:24:00,880 --> 01:24:04,350
1 5 seconds, you're blocked in
or you're paint on the train.

675
01:24:09,040 --> 01:24:10,996
Come on, come on!

676
01:24:11,200 --> 01:24:13,395
Stay on me. This'll be tight!

677
01:24:19,360 --> 01:24:22,591
- Go, go, go.
- You're going to stop there.

678
01:24:59,880 --> 01:25:03,589
- OK, guys, coming into position.
- Stay cool.

679
01:25:15,240 --> 01:25:18,471
Ten, nine...

680
01:25:19,200 --> 01:25:21,953
...eight, seven...

681
01:25:22,160 --> 01:25:24,913
...six, five...

682
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:26,599
...four...

683
01:25:26,800 --> 01:25:28,836
- Don't lose him.
- ...three...

684
01:25:29,400 --> 01:25:32,437
...two, one...

685
01:25:38,280 --> 01:25:39,599
What...?!

686
01:25:53,400 --> 01:25:54,674
Damn.

687
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:04,590
What the fuck happened to my truck?!

688
01:26:09,000 --> 01:26:12,197
- lt blew through the street.
- Get under there.

689
01:26:24,080 --> 01:26:26,913
- We have another problem.
- What?

690
01:26:27,440 --> 01:26:30,830
- This isn't the Worthington 1 000.
- What?

691
01:26:31,040 --> 01:26:33,793
He switched safes on us.

692
01:26:34,000 --> 01:26:36,355
- Can you do it?
- lt's lsraeli made.

693
01:26:36,560 --> 01:26:40,075
lt's got a glass relock system.
There's a pane of glass here.

694
01:26:40,280 --> 01:26:44,876
lf l don't drill perfectly, steel rods
snap into place and we can't open it.

695
01:26:45,080 --> 01:26:47,753
Then we're up shit creek.

696
01:27:16,040 --> 01:27:21,034
l think l just cracked the glass.
l don't think it broke, though.

697
01:27:21,240 --> 01:27:26,268
l can't drill it again.
l have to do it by touch.

698
01:27:28,680 --> 01:27:31,240
l can't get through.
The train's blocking the tunnel.

699
01:27:31,440 --> 01:27:34,113
- Where does the Metro Rail emerge?
- Eleventh and Fig.

700
01:27:34,320 --> 01:27:40,190
Meet at Eleventh and Figaro and double
back to Hollywood and Highland. Hurry.

701
01:27:54,480 --> 01:28:00,669
Baggage for train 22
now available at carousel 4.

702
01:28:38,160 --> 01:28:43,553
l can't do this. l need a drill
or a borescope to get in there.

703
01:28:43,760 --> 01:28:48,390
- Come on, Charlie.
- You can do this.

704
01:29:40,360 --> 01:29:42,430
Slide.

705
01:29:50,280 --> 01:29:54,353
- Don't you want to see inside?
- Absolutely.

706
01:29:58,480 --> 01:30:01,950
Napster, 1 3 across, 4 high, 4 deep.

707
01:30:03,600 --> 01:30:06,990
- That's 208 bricks.
- How much?

708
01:30:13,040 --> 01:30:15,713
- 2.7 million.
- What?!

709
01:30:15,920 --> 01:30:18,309
No, it's 27. That's 27 million.

710
01:30:18,520 --> 01:30:21,990
That's 27 million dollars worth of gold.

711
01:30:28,400 --> 01:30:33,520
Got the Holy Spirit.
You should get on it, it's a good train.

712
01:31:09,880 --> 01:31:12,394
What do you think, John?

713
01:31:19,280 --> 01:31:23,717
- 27 million.
- Say it again.

714
01:31:49,880 --> 01:31:52,110
We've got two motorcycles
on us, Charlie.

715
01:31:54,680 --> 01:31:57,399
Three Minis heading east
towards the LA river.

716
01:31:57,600 --> 01:32:00,751
Stop them
before they get to the street.

717
01:32:04,360 --> 01:32:05,952
Shit!

718
01:32:23,480 --> 01:32:25,869
Here we go.

719
01:32:38,640 --> 01:32:39,914
Open your door.

720
01:32:45,200 --> 01:32:47,270
Come on, guys. We're moving.

721
01:32:51,360 --> 01:32:52,679
There!

722
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:04,514
Hey, come on. Get down!

723
01:33:31,040 --> 01:33:33,235
Come on!

724
01:33:38,800 --> 01:33:40,870
Where are you going?

725
01:33:59,560 --> 01:34:03,109
l'll take Steve. Go to Union Station.
l'll meet you there.

726
01:34:03,920 --> 01:34:05,353
Stay on him.

727
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:16,717
l'm opening up a spot on Lower Grand.

728
01:34:18,880 --> 01:34:21,155
l know it's you, Charlie.

729
01:34:22,320 --> 01:34:24,709
Take your next left.

730
01:35:21,040 --> 01:35:22,598
Nice move, Steve.

731
01:35:59,480 --> 01:36:01,516
Get out! Get out!

732
01:36:01,720 --> 01:36:03,597
l said get out!

733
01:37:34,480 --> 01:37:38,473
- You got Mini Coopers in there, right?
- Look, man...

734
01:37:38,680 --> 01:37:43,231
Don't worry about them. l'll give
you five grand to put me inside.

735
01:37:48,040 --> 01:37:50,873
Buy your girlfriend something nice.

736
01:38:01,600 --> 01:38:04,558
Half now, half when you help me unload.

737
01:38:08,800 --> 01:38:13,191
l've got to hand it to you.
You played this one pretty smart.

738
01:38:13,400 --> 01:38:18,918
Decoy trucks, you switched safes,
the helicopter routine. Pretty good.

739
01:38:19,120 --> 01:38:22,430
Now l've got the gold,
you've got nothing.

740
01:38:22,640 --> 01:38:27,395
l've got this, so cut the crap
and give me my goddamn gold!

741
01:38:40,400 --> 01:38:43,551
- Who are you?
- l am Mashkov.

742
01:38:43,760 --> 01:38:48,993
- You killed my cousin Yevhen.
- You've got to have some insurance.

743
01:38:56,560 --> 01:39:01,395
He was already dead when l arrived.
He dealt with unsavoury people.

744
01:39:01,600 --> 01:39:06,594
- This guy's trying to play you.
- You were right. No imagination.

745
01:39:09,640 --> 01:39:15,556
There's a lot of gold in there. Only we've
got guns. l'll make you a good deal.

746
01:39:21,520 --> 01:39:24,671
l've already made my deal.

747
01:39:28,760 --> 01:39:32,355
- What do you want?
- You know this was never about gold.

748
01:39:32,560 --> 01:39:35,313
Whatever helps you sleep at night,
sweetheart.

749
01:39:39,120 --> 01:39:41,509
Bitch. Charlie, come on, Charlie!

750
01:39:46,120 --> 01:39:47,394
That l loved.

751
01:39:47,600 --> 01:39:51,229
l'll double whatever he's given you,
just don't shoot me.

752
01:39:51,440 --> 01:39:56,355
Don't worry, l'm not going to shoot you.
l'm going to take you to my workplace.

753
01:39:56,560 --> 01:39:59,757
l think you'll be interested
in my machinery.

754
01:40:01,640 --> 01:40:03,437
Oh, come on.

755
01:40:09,200 --> 01:40:12,272
Guys, l want to make a toast.

756
01:40:12,480 --> 01:40:18,749
To John Bridger. The most brilliant
master planner of all. Father and friend.

757
01:40:24,080 --> 01:40:26,913
Stella was right.
lt wasn't about the money.

758
01:40:27,120 --> 01:40:31,318
Of course, that didn't stop the guys
from having some fun.

759
01:40:31,520 --> 01:40:33,750
Handsome Rob got his Aston Martin.

760
01:40:38,280 --> 01:40:41,875
Took it for a ride to break it in.

761
01:40:53,800 --> 01:40:56,234
He got off with a warning.

762
01:40:58,480 --> 01:41:01,631
Left Ear got his dream house in Spain

763
01:41:01,840 --> 01:41:04,718
with a room just for his shoes.

764
01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:16,028
Lyle finally made
the cover of Wired magazine.

765
01:41:18,160 --> 01:41:22,631
- Are you really the Napster?
- Yes, l am.

766
01:41:22,840 --> 01:41:25,877
And he got that kick-ass stereo
he wanted.

767
01:41:26,080 --> 01:41:28,594
Would you listen to something?

768
01:41:28,800 --> 01:41:32,634
With speakers so loud they could
blow a woman's clothes off.

769
01:41:35,760 --> 01:41:38,513
lf you would.

770
01:41:51,920 --> 01:41:55,196
And me?
l took John Bridger's advice.

771
01:41:56,480 --> 01:41:59,278
l found somebody l want to spend
the rest of my life with,

772
01:41:59,480 --> 01:42:02,711
and l'm going
to hold on to her forever.

